The paper deals with planarity testing for clustered graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms. The use of matrices and fixed sides suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG), while the study of planarity fits into the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the complexity of the problem, which could fall under the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) or graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of algorithms and analysis of running time could also place the paper in the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
